Thread on living titanoboas, primordial serpentine beasts of great size, still crawling in the hidden places of the earth.

What if there was a "shadow megafauna" existing today without our knowledge? A few descendants of the titans of the past, who somehow survived many aeons?

Let us start with the story of Percy Fawcett, a British explorer in South America. Percy reported being attacked by and shooting a giant 20 meter / 60 feet long anaconda.

>pic related is his explanation of the event.

from the beast.

In 1973, a bunch of workers there saw 6 meters / 20 feet of a giant snake's tail in a bush before it slithered in hiding.

After the government sent a group to find the monster, the search party discovered 40 cm / 16 inches wide tracks in the ground.

Meanwhile, in Japan, stories of the Yamakachi haunt Mount Tsurugi. Local legends tell that beneath the mountain there is a buried treasure - with a giant snake protecting it from looters.

Villagers believed in the myth quite literally, even carrying weapons to protect themselves
in 1817, in Gloucester, a giant serpent was spotted in the harbor. A few years later, a similar creature reportedly attacked a British ship.

... large as a horse. And those stories are just a few of hundreds from all over the world. Everywhere there are stories of gigantic snakes and serpents, many of the sightings reported being quite recent: so - it seems like some titanic species of snakes still inhabit the earth.

Finally, and most interesting, the 50 foot Congo snake! In 1959, Colonel Remy Van Lierde was flying with a helicopter from a mission when he saw the titanic 16 meter long horror.

The pilot managed to snap a photograph of it. According to him, the head of the snake was as ...

How curious and fascinating! If these monstrosities still live in our world, what other primordial fellas could too be hiding somewhere? Have a good evening fellas, and remember to stay safe when exploring the jungles of the continents.

Statue of Ivan Tankov Kozarev, "The Bear-Wrestler", a Bulgarian revolutionary, strong enough to carry a wooden cannon on his back.

Kidnapped the woman he fell in love with on the same night, survived torture in the worst Ottoman prison and left it alive, died from poison.
